title.narrative: CAPE VERDE - Recovery and Reform of the Electricity Sector Project

description.narrative: The proposed main development objectives of the Recovery and Reform of the Electricity Sector Project (RRESP) are to increase electricity generation in the Islands of Sao Vicente and Santiago and to assist ELECTRA to reduce electricity losses in Santiago Island.

condition.narrative: Finance Agreement :1.Regulatory review of electricity tariff | Description :The Borrower has adopted and made public the AREResolution (Effectiveness Condition). | Due Date :03-May-2012
Finance Agreement :2.Subsidiary Loan Agreement | Description :The Subsidiary Loan Agreement has been executed on behalf of theBorrower and ELECTRA (Effectiveness Condition) | Due Date :03-May-2012

Finance Agreement :3.Adoption of a Project Implementation Manual | Description :The Project Implementation Manual shall have beenadopted by the Borrower in a manner satisfactory to the Bank (Effectiveness Condition) | Due Date :03-May-2012

Finance Agreement :4. Recruitment by ELECTRA of an Environmental and Social specialist | Description :The Borrower shall ensurethat by no later than 30 days from the Effective Date, ELECTRA shall have hired an environmental and social specialist under termsof reference, qualifications and experience satisfactory to the Bank who shall be kept in the position throughout Projectimplementation | Due Date :23-Jun-2012

Finance Agreement :5. Recruitment of external financial auditor for the Project. | Description :The Borrower shall by no later than120 days after the Effective Date, have appointed an external financial auditor for the Projectunder terms of reference andqualifications and experience satisfactory to the Bank | Due Date :23-Nov-2012

Finance Agreement :6. Project implementation unit | Description :The Borrower shall maintain the PIU throughout the implementationof the Project, with functions and resources satisfactory to the Bank | Frequency :Monthly

Finance Agreement :7. Additional Covenant: Electricity tariff level adjustment | Description :The Borrower shall ensure thatelectricity tariff levels are adjusted every four (4) months in order to provide ELECTRA with the maximum allowed revenue set bythe regulatory formula provided in the ARE Regulation or else compensate ELECTRA for any loss of revenue caused by insufficient orlate tariff adjustments | Frequency :Quarterly

Finance Agreement :8. Additional Covenant: Interest Coverage Ratio | Description :The Borrower shall beginning in the secondsemester of 2013 and by no later than November 30 of each Fiscal Year thereafter informthe Bank the estimates of ELECTRA yearlyfinancial results for the current Fiscal Year and the forecasted budget for the following Fiscal Year. | Frequency :Yearly
